# Environment Variables for Amazing Grace Baptist Church Website

Copy this file to `.env.local` and update the values with your actual configuration.

## Database Configuration

# MongoDB (Option 1)
DATABASE_URL="mongodb://localhost:27017/amazing-grace-church"

# Supabase (Option 2) - Recommended for production
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL="https://your-project.supabase.co"
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY="your-supabase-anon-key"
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY="your-supabase-service-role-key"

## Authentication

# NextAuth.js Configuration
NEXTAUTH_SECRET="your-super-secret-key-here"
NEXTAUTH_URL="http://localhost:3000"

# Admin Credentials (for initial setup)
ADMIN_EMAIL="admin@amazinggracechurch.org"
ADMIN_PASSWORD="your-secure-admin-password"

## Email Configuration (for contact forms)

# SMTP Settings (Gmail example)
SMTP_HOST="smtp.gmail.com"
SMTP_PORT="587"
SMTP_USER="your-email@gmail.com"
SMTP_PASS="your-app-password"

# Alternative: SendGrid
SENDGRID_API_KEY="your-sendgrid-api-key"
FROM_EMAIL="noreply@amazinggracechurch.org"

## File Storage

# Supabase Storage (Recommended)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_STORAGE_BUCKET="church-media"

# Alternative: AWS S3
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID="your-aws-access-key"
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY="your-aws-secret-key"
AWS_REGION="us-east-1"
AWS_S3_BUCKET="amazing-grace-church-media"

# Alternative: Cloudinary
CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME="your-cloudinary-cloud-name"
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY="your-cloudinary-api-key"
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET="your-cloudinary-api-secret"

